# Hexagonal Architecture — StyleUp Backend

Complements [architecture.mdc](architecture.mdc). This rule defines **layer placement**, **port/adapter wiring**, and **violations to flag** — not API envelope or auth details.

## Current Repo State (as of scaffolding)

- `src/modules/` — **planned, not created yet** (auth, users, providers, bookings, payments, notifications)
- `src/infra/` — connection adapters only: `database/` (Mongoose), `postgres/` (TypeORM), `redis/` (ioredis)
- **No repository ports or persistence adapters exist yet** — first feature module must establish the pattern below
- **Established DI token pattern:** `REDIS_CLIENT` Symbol in [redis.module.ts](../../src/infra/redis/redis.module.ts) — reuse this for repository ports

---

## Layer Map (actual folders)

| Layer | Location | May import | Must NOT import |
|---|---|---|---|
| **HTTP** | `src/modules/<domain>/*.controller.ts` | service, DTOs, guards/decorators from `common/` | mongoose, typeorm, `@nestjs/mongoose`, `@nestjs/typeorm`, infra adapters, other modules' schemas |
| **Application** | `src/modules/<domain>/*.service.ts` | port interfaces/tokens, domain types, other modules' **exported services** | `@nestjs/mongoose`, `@nestjs/typeorm`, `mongoose`, `typeorm`, anything under `src/infra/persistence/` |
| **Ports** | `src/modules/<domain>/ports/*.port.ts` | domain types, plain TS types | `src/infra/**`, mongoose, typeorm |
| **Domain types** | `src/modules/<domain>/domain/` or `src/shared/types/` | nothing from Nest/ORM | framework packages |
| **Adapters (Mongo)** | `src/infra/persistence/mongoose/<domain>/` | mongoose, module port interface | application services |
| **Adapters (Postgres)** | `src/infra/persistence/postgres/<domain>/` | typeorm, module port interface | application services |
| **Infra bootstrap** | `src/infra/database/`, `postgres/`, `redis/` | framework modules only | feature module code |
| **Cross-cutting** | `src/common/`, `src/config/`, `src/health/` | infra tokens for ops checks | business logic |

> **Note:** [data-schemas.mdc](data-schemas.mdc) globs `*.schema.ts` at module root. For hex alignment, **new** Mongoose schemas belong in `src/infra/persistence/mongoose/<domain>/` with the adapter — not co-located with the service. Flag if a new schema is added under `src/modules/` without a port/adapter split.

---

## Dependency Flow

```
Controller → Application Service → Port (interface + token) → Adapter (Mongoose | TypeORM)
```

- Controllers: validate HTTP input (DTO), call service, map to response DTO — **zero business logic**
- Services: orchestrate use cases; depend on **port tokens only**
- Adapters: implement ports; own all ORM/schema/entity code

---

## NestJS Port DI Pattern (required)

Plain TypeScript interfaces **do not exist at runtime**. Every port needs:

1. **Port interface** — `src/modules/<domain>/ports/<domain>.repository.port.ts`
2. **Injection token** — `Symbol` constant exported alongside the interface
3. **Adapter class** — implements the interface, lives in `src/infra/persistence/`
4. **Module registration** — `{ provide: TOKEN, useClass: Adapter }` in the feature module

### Canonical example — established token pattern (Redis)

From [redis.module.ts](../../src/infra/redis/redis.module.ts) + [redis.health.ts](../../src/health/redis.health.ts):

```typescript
// infra/redis/redis.module.ts
export const REDIS_CLIENT = Symbol('REDIS_CLIENT');

// health/redis.health.ts
constructor(@Inject(REDIS_CLIENT) private readonly redis: Redis) {}
```

### Template for first domain repository (**NEW — copy when scaffolding providers**)

```typescript
// src/modules/providers/ports/provider.repository.port.ts
export interface ProviderRepositoryPort {
  findById(id: string): Promise<Provider | null>;
}

export const PROVIDER_REPOSITORY = Symbol('PROVIDER_REPOSITORY');

// src/infra/persistence/mongoose/providers/mongoose-provider.repository.ts
@Injectable()
export class MongooseProviderRepository implements ProviderRepositoryPort {
  constructor(@InjectModel(Provider.name) private readonly model: Model<ProviderDocument>) {}
  async findById(id: string): Promise<Provider | null> { /* map document → domain */ }
}

// src/modules/providers/providers.module.ts
@Module({
  imports: [MongooseModule.forFeature([{ name: Provider.name, schema: ProviderSchema }])],
  providers: [
    ProvidersService,
    { provide: PROVIDER_REPOSITORY, useClass: MongooseProviderRepository },
  ],
  exports: [ProvidersService],
})
export class ProvidersModule {}

// src/modules/providers/providers.service.ts
@Injectable()
export class ProvidersService {
  constructor(
    @Inject(PROVIDER_REPOSITORY) private readonly providers: ProviderRepositoryPort,
  ) {}
}
```

For Postgres-backed aggregates, mirror with `TypeOrmProviderRepository` in `src/infra/persistence/postgres/<domain>/` and register the same `PROVIDER_REPOSITORY` token (one adapter per aggregate — do not mix ORMs behind one port unless explicitly designed).

