## Dual Database Rules

Both ORMs coexist at infra bootstrap level:

| Store | Bootstrap | Adapter home | Use for |
|---|---|---|---|
| **MongoDB** | [database.module.ts](../../src/infra/database/database.module.ts) | `src/infra/persistence/mongoose/` | Document/geo-heavy domain (providers, availability) per existing schema rules |
| **Postgres** | [postgres.module.ts](../../src/infra/postgres/postgres.module.ts) | `src/infra/persistence/postgres/` | Relational/transactional data (new TypeORM entities + migrations in `src/migrations/`) |

- Application services **never** choose Mongo vs Postgres — the module wires one adapter per port
- Migrations CLI uses [data-source.ts](../../data-source.ts) — adapters must not bypass this for schema changes

---

## Service Import Violation Rule

**If a file under `src/modules/**/` named `*.service.ts` imports any of:**

- `@nestjs/mongoose`, `@nestjs/typeorm`, `mongoose`, `typeorm`

→ **Flag as a hexagonal violation.** Do not silently refactor without user confirmation. Suggest extracting an adapter behind a port.

Controllers with the same imports are also violations (except thin `forFeature` registration stays in `*.module.ts`, never in `*.service.ts`).

---

## Validation Ownership

| Concern | Layer | Mechanism | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| HTTP input shape | Controller boundary | `class-validator` on request DTOs + global `ValidationPipe` | `@IsString()`, `@IsISO8601()` |
| Authorization | Controller boundary | Guards (`@UseGuards`, `@Roles`) | Never manual JWT checks in controller body |
| Domain invariants | Application / domain | Service or domain entity method | `endTime > startTime`, slot conflict rules |
| Persistence constraints | Adapter | Schema indexes, DB constraints | `2dsphere`, unique compound indexes |

DTO validation **≠** business rules. A valid DTO can still be rejected by the service for domain reasons.

